body:
# Linear Project Management

Projects group related issues into larger initiatives. They can span multiple teams and provide high-level progress tracking.

## Querying Projects

```graphql
query Projects {
  projects(
    filter: { state: { in: ["started", "planned"] } }
    first: 25
    orderBy: updatedAt
  ) {
    nodes {
      id
      name
      description
      state
      progress
      targetDate
      startDate
      lead {
        name
      }
      teams {
        nodes {
          name
          key
        }
      }
      issues {
        nodes {
          identifier
          title
          state {
            name
            type
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

With the SDK:

```typescript
import { LinearClient } from "@linear/sdk";

const client = new LinearClient({ apiKey: process.env.LINEAR_API_KEY });

const projects = await client.projects({
  filter: { state: { in: ["started", "planned"] } },
});

for (const project of projects.nodes) {
  console.log(`${project.name} — ${project.state} (${Math.round(project.progress * 100)}%)`);
}
```

## Creating a Project

```graphql
mutation CreateProject($input: ProjectCreateInput!) {
  projectCreate(input: $input) {
    success
    project {
      id
      name
      url
    }
  }
}
```

Variables:

```json
{
  "input": {
    "name": "Q3 Platform Rewrite",
    "description": "Rewrite core platform services for scalability",
    "teamIds": ["team-uuid-1", "team-uuid-2"],
    "leadId": "user-uuid",
    "targetDate": "2026-09-30",
    "state": "planned"
  }
}
```

With the SDK:

```typescript
const result = await client.createProject({
  name: "Q3 Platform Rewrite",
  description: "Rewrite core platform services for scalability",
  teamIds: [engTeam.id, infraTeam.id],
  leadId: leadUser.id,
  targetDate: "2026-09-30",
  state: "planned",
});

if (result.success) {
  const project = await result.project;
  console.log(`Created: ${project.name} — ${project.url}`);
}
```

## Updating a Project

```typescript
const result = await client.updateProject("PROJECT_UUID", {
  state: "started",
  description: "Updated scope: includes API and frontend",
});
```

## Adding Issues to a Project

Associate an issue with a project by setting `projectId` when creating or updating the issue:

```typescript
// When creating
await client.createIssue({
  teamId: team.id,
  title: "Implement new auth flow",
  projectId: project.id,
});

// When updating
await client.updateIssue(issue.id, {
  projectId: project.id,
});
```

## Project Status

| Status | Meaning |
|--------|----------|
| `backlog` | Not yet planned |
| `planned` | Scheduled but not started |
| `started` | Actively in progress |
| `paused` | Temporarily on hold |
| `completed` | Finished successfully |
| `cancelled` | Abandoned |

## Project Updates

Post progress updates to a project:

```graphql
mutation PostProjectUpdate {
  projectUpdateCreate(input: {
    projectId: "PROJECT_UUID"
    body: "## Week 12 Update\n\nCompleted auth service migration. Frontend work starts next week."
    health: "onTrack"
  }) {
    success
    projectUpdate {
      id
      createdAt
    }
  }
}
```

Health values: `onTrack`, `atRisk`, `offTrack`.

## Progress Tracking

The `progress` field (0.0 to 1.0) is automatically calculated from the ratio of completed issues to total issues in the project. You can also query `issues` on the project to compute custom metrics.

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `LINEAR_API_KEY` | Personal API key for authentication |
